rPublicProfile?gid=elfnom>Elfnom</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 23<br> <font color=#333333>(1/23/03 6:39:07 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowergeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=8555.topic>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   New GE Force 4 video card</span><hr size=1> <br>
  I've been reading that GE Force 4 cards are out now with 128 megs of memory on board.  Believe they sell for about $275 to $300.  Has anyone upgraded with one of these yet?  I was just wondering if that will help remove lag in places like the bazaar.  Think I'm running the GE Force 2 right now.  It works ok in most zones, but gets pretty laggy in the bazaar and with a lot of spell casting going out in some places.  I wouldn't want to spend that much if it doesn't make a big improvement. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=lamillimal>Lamil Limal</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 5<br> <font color=#333333>(1/23/03 6:47:25 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowergeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=8555.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: New GE Force 4 video card</span><hr size=1> I am currently running the GeForce 4 4600 TI with 128mb DDR ram onboard.  It gives a huge improvement on things like lag in the bazaar.  Although i still do lose fps in the bazaar, i can now run freely around with all graphics enabled.  Hope this helps out for you.  BTW, the best thing you can do for lag reduction is to get a DSL or cable connection if at all possible, this will be the most dramatic improvement of all. <p>Lamil Limal<br>
56 Pez Dispenser of Tunare</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=elfnom>Elfnom</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 24<br> <font color=#333333>(1/23/03 6:56:03 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowergeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=8555.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Cable modem</span><hr size=1> <br>
  Hmmm.  You bring up a good point.  I'm on a cable modem, but we have 3 different bandwidth options on our cable system and I have the slowest one.  Think it's about 4 times faster than dialup.  Wonder if it's better to upgrade the video card, or just move up to the fastest cable connection?<br>
  When I first starting playing, I had a Celeron PC with integrated graphics.  First time I went to Luclin, I could hardly move.  I bought a new computer with a separate video card and that made a big improvement.  Bazaar is now the worst place.  I turn clip plane all the way down there and that helps quite a bit.   <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=talusini>Talusini</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Conjurer</span><br>  Posts: 220<br> <font color=#333333>(1/23/03 6:56:28 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowergeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=8555.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www3.sympatico.ca/talusar/Talusini.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: New GE Force 4 video card</span><hr size=1> The rest of the game runs MUCH better on my GeForce Ti4600 as opposed to my GeForce3 and that alone is worth the upgrade from whatever card you are upgrading from.  As far as the bazaar is concerned, I still have to turn the clip plane all the way down and stare are the floor if I want to play around with my inventory/bank.<br>
<br>
I COULD run with full clip, but you end up running into walls or facing the wrong direction...<br>
<br>
Hope that helps! <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=411018&amp;resize=true&quot;" target="_new">Talusini Petuccini</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END-->Arch Mage - Master of the Elements<!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END-->Tunare</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=wrathen@themagicianstower>Wrathen</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 41<br> <font color=#333333>(1/23/03 7:04:51 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowergeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=8555.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   don't forget ram</span><hr size=1> RAM is also a big part of this<br>
